(Test format string precision and floating point expressions)

(Float precision with expressions)
a float called "pi" is 3.14159265358979.
a float called "half" is 0.5.
Print "pi: {pi:.2}".
Print "pi: {pi:.4}".
Print "pi: {pi:.0}".
Print "pi/2: {pi divide 2:.3}".
Print "pi*2: {pi multiply 2:.3}".

(Expressions with formatting)
a number called "price" is 19.
a number called "tax_rate" is 0.08.
Print "Price: ${price}".
Print "Tax: ${price multiply tax_rate:.2}".
Print "Total: ${price add price multiply tax_rate:.2}".

(Percentage calculations)
a float called "ratio" is 0.756.
a float called "completion" is 0.333333.
Print "Progress: {ratio multiply 100:.1}%".
Print "Complete: {completion multiply 100:.0}%".
Print "Remaining: {100 subtract completion multiply 100:.1}%".
